rComments: PHY151 was a great course. He explained stuff in a very unique way. He also answers questions during the lecture. On the other hand, midterm and final was really hard.

Overall Prof. James is a great professor and dude. He really cares about his students, always encourages us to come to office hours. What's best about him is that he's very passionate about what he teaches, and even dedicated part of a lecture to us just asking him about random subjects of physics we were curious about. He also curbs marks often.
I really enjoyed his lectures because he is able to keep the class well engaged throughout
Great prof, I learned a lot in the course. However the final was really tough.

Absolutely a good professor. However, the final exam is tough as hell! Anybody who wants to take this course next year, just remember one thing. The problem set and the course content is easy, you can understand them well. But the level of difficulty of the exam is really sacred. Take time to do every past midterm tests and exam.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: The class was bomb, the prof and TAs made it even better. Some people took it as an elective, and I strongly encourage it if you're good at math, cuz there's a bunch of nasty proofs. Homeworks were easy, practicals tough, but bearable, midterm was hard and final even harder, but resources to get ready are available, and everyone is willing to help!
Lectures were always interesting and funny. He really cared about his students too. It was confusing sometimes, but reading the textbook helped clarify lecture notes. Would recommend.

Teaching is amazing and funny, but he oversimplified a lot of things and reply a little bit too much on math. I think for average student his lecture is very good and clear. If you want to discuss things further, he is always happy to talk to you!

AMAZING PROF!! he is incredibly funny and gives clear detailed lectures. Very enjoyable class. Beware that problem sets are not a good indication of test difficulty they do give you the past tests so make sure u know those very well. Hope to have him as a prof again.

Professor James is an amazing lecturer! He was a little intimidating to ask questions to during class but after class or in office hours he was very approachable! On top of this, his lectures were almost always very clear. In class examples were extremely helpful! Highly recommend taking a course with him.

Professor James taught all of the lectures for PHY151 which included mechanics, energy, relativity, and rotational dynamics. His lectures are always funny and informative, and he explains examples from previous exams. Although his exams are difficult, the questions are fair if the concepts are understood. There are also mark adjustments at the end.

This professor is horrible. He is so confident to the point that he is absolutely arrogant. He complicates simple topics into extremely complicated equations and solutions and says, "everyone happy?" every now and then when there's 100% "I dont get this" face in front of him. No one would be brave enough to ask questions when you teach like that
Gives unfair tests. Puts minimal effort into making lectures and other course material. Hired a TA that was far more of a hindrance than a help.
Reminds me of Mary Poppins. Love this guy!
Amazing British professor. Every lecture is at the same time very interesting and funny. Really loved that course

That British class! Funniest professor ever. Only course for which I sought help at office hours and he's really helpful. Be warned that his tests are very, very hard. This professor will openly admit that the course is curved though "DUNWORRY Y'ALL BE CURVED AT THE END"
prof is an ok explainer, funny and classy british guy

The stuff is way too easy if u're prepared enough for university. Not much calculus involved makes the course a little boring. He's clear with what he wants to convey, but not so impressive. I guess the only use of lectures, is to get an idea of what to expect on exams. If u don't care about grades, just read Feynman's lectures and u'll learn more.
A really good prof
awesome professor
9/10. By far the best teacher I have.
Such a character, the tests and problem sets were at times challenging, but I learned a lot.
unclear.
